<div class="container mt-4">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8 mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-center mb-4">About Dog Adoption System</h1>
      
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3>Project Overview</h3>
          <p>This Ruby on Rails application manages a comprehensive dog adoption system using data from multiple reliable sources to provide accurate and up-to-date information about dogs available for adoption.</p>

          <h3>Data Sources</h3>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
              <div class="card border-primary h-100">
                <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                  <h5 class="mb-0">1. Dog API</h5>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                  <p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="https://dog.ceo/dog-api/" target="_blank">dog.ceo/dog-api</a></p>
                  <p><strong>Data:</strong> Real dog breed information and authentic breed images</p>
                  <p class="mt-auto"><strong>Usage:</strong> Populates our Dogs table with <%= Dog.count %> dogs from <%= Dog.distinct.count(:breed) %> different breeds</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
              <div class="card border-success h-100">
                <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
                  <h5 class="mb-0">2. Faker Gem - Owners</h5>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                  <p><strong>Source:</strong> Ruby Faker Gem</p>
                  <p><strong>Data:</strong> Realistic owner contact information</p>
                  <p class="mt-auto"><strong>Usage:</strong> Generated <%= Owner.count %> potential adopters with names, emails, addresses, and phone numbers</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12">
              <div class="card border-warning h-100">
                <div class="card-header bg-warning text-white">
                  <h5 class="mb-0">3. Faker Gem - Adoptions</h5>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                  <p><strong>Source:</strong> Ruby Faker Gem</p>
                  <p><strong>Data:</strong> Adoption history and records</p>
                  <p class="mt-auto"><strong>Usage:</strong> Created <%= Adoption.count %> adoption records with dates, fees, and notes</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Database Structure</h3>
          <div class="table-responsive">
            <table class="table table-striped">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Table</th>
                  <th>Purpose</th>
                  <th>Key Fields</th>
                  <th>Record Count</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Dogs</strong></td>
                  <td>Store dog information and availability</td>
                  <td>breed, name, age, image_url, description, available_for_adoption</td>
                  <td><%= Dog.count %></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Owners</strong></td>
                  <td>Manage adopter contact information</td>
                  <td>name, email, phone, address, city, state, zip_code</td>
                  <td><%= Owner.count %></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Adoptions</strong></td>
                  <td>Track adoption history and relationships</td>
                  <td>dog_id, owner_id, adoption_date, adoption_fee, notes</td>
                  <td><%= Adoption.count %></td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h3>Relationships</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Many-to-Many:</strong> Dogs and Owners through Adoptions (a dog can be adopted by an owner, and owners can adopt multiple dogs)</li>
            <li><strong>One-to-Many:</strong> Dogs have many Adoptions</li>
            <li><strong>One-to-Many:</strong> Owners have many Adoptions</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Current Statistics</h3>
          <div class="row g-2">
            <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
              <div class="card bg-info text-white text-center">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h4><%= Dog.where(available_for_adoption: true).count %></h4>
                  <p class="mb-0">Available Dogs</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
              <div class="card bg-secondary text-white text-center">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h4><%= Dog.where(available_for_adoption: false).count %></h4>
                  <p class="mb-0">Adopted Dogs</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
              <div class="card bg-success text-white text-center">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h4><%= Owner.count %></h4>
                  <p class="mb-0">Registered Owners</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-3 col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
              <div class="card bg-warning text-white text-center">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h4><%= Adoption.count %></h4>
                  <p class="mb-0">Total Adoptions</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>